@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<div class="card shadow mt-3">
    <div class="card-body">
        <h4>We collect your data</h4>
        <p>
            Yes, we collect your name, email, GPA, English level, marital status,
            and literally everything else you put in your profile.
            We promise not to sell it. Probably.
        </p>

        <h4>Cookies</h4>
        <p>
            We use cookies. Not the chocolate chip kind, unfortunately.
            Just the boring authentication kind that keeps you logged in.
        </p>

        <h4>Your rights</h4>
        <p>
            You have the right to remain silent.
            Anything you type into your profile can and will be used
            against you in a CV review.
        </p>

        <h4>Security</h4>
        <p>
            Your password is hashed with a secure algorithm.
            We have no idea what your password is.
            Neither does anyone else. Including you, probably.
        </p>

        <h4>Contact</h4>
        <p>
            If you have any concerns about your privacy,
            please write them on a piece of paper and throw it away.
            Or email us. We might respond.
        </p>

        <hr />
        <p class="text-muted small">
            Last updated: never. This policy is eternal and immutable,
            like the laws of physics, but less reliable.
            &copy; @DateTime.Now.Year Abay Tolegen. No rights reserved whatsoever.
        </p>
    </div>
</div>